{
  "stem": "3212.4",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They-- they go in, and they close the doors in the crematorium.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And then the-- the-- the SS looks in the hole to see how-- and the strong people crawled on top of the other ones to the top, when they put the gas in.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] And then, after they-- they gassed, they opened the doors.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And then the Sonderkommando put them in the ovens to burn them.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Suddenly, we became-- we became, in-- in-- in Mannerlager, adults, Walter and me.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I had-- we had to start working.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I worked with Walter, I think, in the-- the Rollwagenkommando. 10 or 12 children-- I don't remember-- we had to take a wagon from horses.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And-- and as horses, we children had to pull the wagon.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "We went out, first off, in the morning, the appels, and then with the wagon we had to go out and then load it with clothing or woods for the crematorium.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And next to us, the kapos were going with-- with the sticks and hitting us.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And we had-- we had to push the wheel so it rolled.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "It was so hard-- children-- hungry.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "On the-- on the road, on the side, was-- was growing green raspberries, and we-- we took them.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "We ate green raspberries.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "It was so hard.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Every time out, and then standing appels.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] In-- in the Rollwagen, I don't know how long I worked-- Walter and me.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And all the other children that were with us were-- most of them were Czechs, from Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And Walter and me, we were the only ones from Austria.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And they-- they were a little bit separated.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "Even we were Jewish, but they called us the [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
